title: Live From Rotterdam: Grand Final
text:
Live From Rotterdam: Grand Final
The Grand Final of the 65th Eurovision Song Contest will take place on May 22 at Rotterdam Ahoy in Rotterdam, the Netherlands. 39 artists will take to the stage over three nights to perform their contributions for the contest, fighting to become the winner of the Eurovision Song Contest 2021.
Today sees the first dress rehearsal for the Grand Final of the Eurovision Song Contest 2021. The dress rehearsal is the final opportunity before the jury show for delegations to make the final tweaks to their performance. The dress rehearsal is scheduled to last for just over 3 and a half hours.
The running order for the performances are as follows:
1. Cyprus
2. Albania
3. Israel
4. Belgium
5. Russia
6. Malta
7. Portugal
8. Serbia
9. United Kingdom
10. Greece
11. Switzerland
12. Iceland
13. Spain
14. Moldova
15. Germany
16. Finland
17. Bulgaria
18. Lithuania
19. Ukraine
20. France
21. Azerbaijan
22. Norway
23. Netherlands
24. Italy
25. Sweden
26. San Marino
LIVE COVERAGE | Live Blog In Progress
13:02 CET // The show opens with a montage of people across Europe looking at a bright light, concluding with Duncan Laurence in the LED House
13:06 CET // The colours of the flags and country names are shown on the LED screens as the acts enter the stage. Chantal, Jan and Edsilia sing whilst Peter Gabriel DJs
13:07 CET // Dadi and Gagnamagnid are shown on a house shaped screen.
13:09 CET // Our four hosts, Edsilia, Chantal, Jan and Nikkie have entered the stage.
13:11 CET // Edsilia and Jan explain how to vote, which is then repeated by Chantal.
Cyprus: Elena Tsagrinou – “El Diablo”
13:12 CET // Chantal is using the time gap created by the time setting up Cyprus by promoting eurovision.tv.
13:14 CET // Elena has just started her first rehearsal of the day.
Albania: Anxhela Peristeri – “Karma”
13:17 CET // Anxhela’s postcard is filmed on a bridge in Maastricht. The LED house is set like a restaurant table with a menu laying on the table which reads “Dinner by Anxhela”
13:18 CET // Anxhela has just started her first rehearsal of the day
Israel: Eden Alene – “Set Me Free”
13:21 CET // Eden’s postcard is filmed in Utrecht
13:21 CET // Eden has just started her first rehearsal of the day
Belgium: Hooverphonic – “The Wrong Place”
13:24 CET // Hooverphonic’s postcard was filmed in Bourtange.
13:25 CET // Hooverphonic have just started their first rehearsal of the day.
Russia: Manizha – “Russian Woman”
13:28 CET // Manizha’s postcard was filmed in ‘s-Hertogenbosch.
13:29 CET // Manizha has just started her first rehearsal of the day.
Malta: Destiny – “Je Me Casse”
13:33 CET // Destiny’s postcard was filmed in Vilssingen in Zeeland.
13:34 CET // Destiny has just started her first rehearsal of the day. She is wearing the same dress as in her Semi Final performance.
